Esparza refused the plea deal on November 20, saying, 'The principle of what they're asking me is to plead guilty to something that they know I am not responsible for,' she said.

She
 will now face trial for one felony count of special circumstance murder
 - a charge that can carry a life sentence without parole.

Prosecutors are calling the murder of Gonzalo Ramirez a 'revenge killing.'

They allege that on 15 April, 1995, a 20-year-old Esparza was at a bar with a group of friends 
including former boyfriend Gianni Van, when she pointed out Ramirez, 
claiming he had raped her in her dorm room at Pomona College a few 
months earlier.

